com.solacesystems.jcsmp.impl

Interface MessageDispatcher


  • public interface MessageDispatcher
    Groups the dispatch operations which allow client applications to further de-multiplex messages matching certain subscriptions. In a nutshell, this feature works as follows: - Given a MessageDispatcher instance (such as JCSMPSession or FlowReceiver), client applications can further add interest to receive messages matching certain subscriptions. This interest can either be through an asynchronous notification or blocking receive operation on a queueing point. - Client applications can also specify whether these subscriptions are local to the SDK only or exported on the router - For example (pseudo-code used below): 1. Create a Session 2. Subscribe to a wildcard topic 'cars/>' 3. Subscribe using a local dispatch only option for 'cars/gm' and 'cars/honda' 4. In this case, messages matching the dispatch subscriptions will be delivered directly to the registered consumers, all other messages matching 'cars/>' are delivered to the default consumer
